sql:
SELECT title, director
FROM movies
WHERE awards_count = (SELECT MAX(awards_count) FROM movies);

external_knowledge:
- 'Scribes who have woven the most stories' refers to writers with the highest number of movies;
- 'Fabric of cinema' is a metaphor for the extensive body of movies in the cinema world;
- 'Fare in the eyes of critics' refers to the average rating of their movies, indicating how well their works are regarded.

- 'dazzling stars' refers to highly-rated movies;
- 'maestro' and 'mastermind' represent the director of the movies;
- 'threshold of excellence' implies a rating above 8;
- 'luminescent era' refers to the year when the movie was released;
- 'spectacle' is used metaphorically to describe the genre of the movies.

